diff --git a/SEMANTIC-SEARCH.md b/SEMANTIC-SEARCH.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..90d95674
--- /dev/null
+++ b/SEMANTIC-SEARCH.md
@@ -0,0 +1,128 @@
+# Semantic Search in Piveau Hub Search
+
+This document describes the implementation of semantic search features in piveau-hub-search, including dataset enrichment with embeddings and hybrid search capabilities.
+
+## Overview
+
+Semantic search enhances traditional keyword-based search by understanding the intent and contextual meaning of search queries. In this implementation, we use vector embeddings to represent both documents (DCAT datasets) and search queries in the same high-dimensional space, allowing for similarity-based retrieval.
+
+The core components of the semantic search feature are:
+- **Embedding Service**: A service to generate vector representations from text.
+- **Dataset Enrichment**: Automatically generating and storing embeddings for DCAT datasets.
+- **Hybrid Search**: Combining traditional BM25 full-text search with k-nearest neighbors (kNN) vector search.
+
+---
+
+## Components and Features
+
+### 1. Embedding Service
+The `EmbeddingService` is responsible for communicating with an external embedding provider (Ollama) to transform text into numerical vectors.
+
+- **Implementation**: `src/main/java/io/piveau/hub/search/services/embeddings/EmbeddingServiceImpl.java`
+- **Model**: By default, it uses the `paraphrase-multilingual` embedding model via Ollama, as it supports german and english languages quite well.
+- **Main Methods**:
+    - `generateEmbedding(String text)`: Converts a string into a semantic vector (float array).
+    - `enrichDatasetWithEmbeddings(JsonObject dataset)`: Extracts relevant text fields from a dataset and adds an `embedding` field.
+    - **Extraction Logic**: The service extracts text from `title`, `description`, and `keywords` dataset fields. For multilingual fields, it prioritizes languages in the order: `_lang` (original), `de`, `en`. For keywords, it collects all non-blank `label` values.
+
+### 2. Dataset Enrichment
+To enable semantic search, DCAT datasets must be enriched with vector embeddings. 
+
+- **Manual Enrichment (Bulk)**: A dedicated background job can be triggered to enrich all existing DCAT datasets in the Elasticsearch index. This is the recommended way to generate embeddings.
+- **Automatic Enrichment**: Note that automatic enrichment during individual dataset creation or updates is currently **disabled** in the code due to high AI model pressure and related timeout problems.
+- **Triggering Enrichment**: Use the `triggerDatasetEmbeddingEnrichment` command in the service shell or send an authorized POST request to `/bulk/datasets/embeddings`. 
+- **Fields**: The service currently targets the following fields to build the embedding context:
+    - `title`: Extracted using language priority (`_lang`, `de`, `en`).
+    - `description`: Extracted using language priority (`_lang`, `de`, `en`).
+    - `keywords`: Extracted from the `label` of each keyword entry.
+
+### 3. Hybrid Search
+Hybrid search combines the strengths of keyword matching and semantic cosinus-similarity.
+
+- **Implementation**: The core logic is integrated into `SearchRequestBuilder.buildHybridSearchRequest`.
+- **Logic**: It combines a semantic query (using `ScriptScoreQuery` and `cosineSimilarity`) with a standard lexical query. This integration ensures that all standard search features like sorting, facets, and filters are also applied to hybrid searches.
+- **Fields**: Semantic matching is performed on embedding fields (`title_embedding`, `description_embedding`, `keywords_embedding`).
+- **Scoring**: Scores from both semantic and lexical methods are combined. A `min_score` and `boost` are applied to the semantic part to ensure relevance.
+
+### 4. API Integration
+The semantic search functionality and its management are exposed via the piveau-hub-search API.
+
+- **Search Endpoint**: `/search` (e.g., `https://localhost:8084/search?q=weather&semanticSearch=true`)
+- **Parameter**: `semanticSearch` (boolean, default: true).
+  If enabled, the search service generates an embedding for the query string `q` and performs a hybrid search. If disabled, the search is performed as a standard full-text search.  Enabled by default to ensure backward compatibility with existing clients, e.g. with Web-UI. 
+- **Bulk Enrichment Endpoint**: `/bulk/datasets/embeddings` (POST)
+  Triggers a background process to enrich all datasets with embeddings. Requires authentication.
+- **OpenAPI**: Updated and specified in `src/main/resources/webroot/openapi.yaml`.
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+The following configurations were introduced or updated:
+
+- **Ollama Integration**: Managed via `docker-compose.yaml`. It spins up an Ollama container with the required model.
+- **Service Configuration**: `PIVEAU_HUB_SEARCH_EMBEDDING_CONFIG` in `conf/config.sample.json` defines the endpoint and model for the Ollama embedding service.
+- **Log Level**: `PIVEAU_LOG_LEVEL` can be used to enable debug logging for the search components.
+
+---
+
+## Building and Running
+
+To build and run the `piveau-hub-search` service with semantic search capabilities, follow these steps:
+
+### 1. Start Prerequisites
+First, you need to start Elasticsearch and Ollama. This is typically done using Docker:
+
+```bash
+docker-compose up -d
+```
+
+This will start Elasticsearch (for storage and vector search) and Ollama (for embedding generation). Inject harvested DCAT datasets into Elasticsearch, e.g. by using the piveau-hub harvesting pipeline or restoring from a backup e.g. via tools like `elasticdump`.
+
+### 2. Build the Service
+Use Maven to compile and package the service into a runnable JAR file:
+
+```bash
+mvn clean package -DskipTests
+```
+
+### 3. Enable Dynamic Mapping
+Setting `dynamic: true` enables dynamic mapping, allowing Elasticsearch to automatically index new embedding fields without schema modifications.
+
+```
+PUT /dataset_write/_mapping
+{
+  "dynamic": true
+}
+```
+
+### 4. Run the Service
+Once the JAR file is generated, you can start the service using:
+
+```bash
+PIVEAU_LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG OTEL_SDK_DISABLED=true java -jar target/search.jar
+```
+*Note: This will execute the JAR with the necessary environment variables (e.g., `PIVEAU_LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG`, `OTEL_SDK_DISABLED=true`).*
+
+---
+
